  <section class="spec-sec" id="s10">
    <h2><span class="num">10</span>CLI</h2>
    <p>Three stages, run in order. The ZIP export is the primary source; add <code>--url</code> for image resolution and <code>--crawl</code> for SEO metadata.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage · substack → astro</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> substack <span class="fl">--export</span> ./export.zip <span class="fl">--url</span> https://my-pub.substack.com <span class="fl">--to</span> ./astro-project
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage transform <span class="fl">--schema</span> content-collections <span class="fl">--content</span> markdown
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--images</span> assets <span class="fl">--redirects</span> netlify</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Values</th><th>Default</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--export</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td>—</td><td>Substack ZIP export file. Required.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--url</span></td><td><span class="ty">url</span></td><td>—</td><td>Publication URL. Required for image download and link rewriting.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--crawl</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Scrape live pages for <code>og:image</code>, <code>og:description</code>, and author metadata.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--route-base</span></td><td><span class="ty">string</span></td><td><span class="ty">/blog</span></td><td>Blog route prefix. Use <code>/</code> to flatten.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--hero</span></td><td><span class="ty">og-image · first-image · none</span></td><td><span class="ty">og-image</span></td><td>How <code>heroImage</code> is derived. <code>og-image</code> requires <code>--crawl</code>; falls back to <code>first-image</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--content</span></td><td><span class="ty">markdown · mdx</span></td><td><span class="ty">markdown</span></td><td>Body format &amp; block handling.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--images</span></td><td><span class="ty">assets · public · localize-external</span></td><td><span class="ty">assets</span></td><td>Image placement strategy.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--podcast-audio</span></td><td><span class="ty">remote · download</span></td><td><span class="ty">remote</span></td><td>Leave audio URLs remote or download to <code>public/audio/</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--subscribe-link</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td><span class="ty">#/portal/signup</span></td><td>Replace Substack subscribe buttons with this link. Use <code>--no-subscribe-buttons</code> to remove entirely.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--include-drafts</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Carry unpublished posts as <code>draft: true</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--include-threads</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Carry thread-type posts. Excluded by default.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--dry-run</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Plan &amp; diff only; write nothing.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s11">
    <h2><span class="num">11</span>Verification</h2>
    <p>Every crossing is auditable. The dry-run reconciles the ZIP content against the output so you can see exactly what moves and what needs review.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Dry-run first</strong> — <code>--dry-run</code> prints the plan and a diff; nothing is written.</li>
      <li><strong>CSV ↔ HTML reconciliation</strong> — the manifest records whether each post had both a CSV row and an HTML file. Gaps (CSV-only or HTML-only) are listed explicitly.</li>
      <li><strong>Image download audit</strong> — every image URL is tested for reachability before download. 404s are listed with the post they belong to so you can identify broken references.</li>
      <li><strong>Counted on, counted off</strong> — extract and load counts are reconciled; any delta (skipped drafts, paid-only content, broken images) is listed explicitly.</li>
      <li><strong>Mention audit</strong> — every mention span found is listed with the extracted <code>@name</code>. Malformed mentions are flagged.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage load --dry-run</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw"><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--dry-run</span>
<span class="out">→ 84 posts → 84 files               ✓ reconciled</span>
<span class="out">→ 3 pages → 3 files                 ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 2 podcasts → 2 files              ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 5 threads (skipped)               ⚠ use --include-threads to carry</span>
<span class="out">→ 142 images → 128 unique           ✓ deduped</span>
<span class="out">→ 3 image 404s                      ⚠ publication may be gone; remote refs preserved</span>
<span class="out">→ 12 /p/ redirects mapped           ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 6 paid posts gated                ⚠ review access: paid</span>
<span class="out">→ 4 mentions converted              ✓</span>
<span class="out">→ 0 unresolved references           ✓ nothing left on the dock</span></pre>
    </div>
  </section>
